### =====================================================
### 5. INVENTORY FUNCTIONS
### =====================================================

### getAvailableStock — P1/W1
### expect: 28 (30 - 2)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/getAvailableStock(productID='P1',warehouseID='W1')

###

### getAvailableStock — P2/W1
### expect: 45 (50 - 5)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/getAvailableStock(productID='P2',warehouseID='W1')

###

### getAvailableStock — 404 test
### expect: 404 Stock not found
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/getAvailableStock(productID='INVALID',warehouseID='W1')

###

### getLowStockAlerts — default (below MinStockLevel)
### expect: S7 (P4/W1 stock=3 < min=5) and S8 (P5/W1 stock=5 < min=8)
GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/getLowStockAlerts()



### expect:
### S2 (P1/W2 stock=10)
### S4 (P2/W2 stock=0)
### S7 (P4/W1 stock=3)
### S8 (P5/W1 stock=5)
  GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/getLowStockAlerts(threshold=15)


### =====================================================
### 6. GOODS RECEIPT — stock increases
### =====================================================

### Receipt P4/W1 qty=20 — restocks low item
### expect: S7 CurrentStock 3 → 23
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/goodsReceipt
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P4",
  "warehouseID": "W1",
  "qty": 20,
  "movedBy": "CoachA"
}

###

### Receipt P1/W1 qty=5
### expect: S1 CurrentStock 30 → 35
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/goodsReceipt
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P1",
  "warehouseID": "W1",
  "qty": 5,
  "movedBy": "CoachA"
}

###

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/StockLevels
### verify: S1 CurrentStock=35, S7 CurrentStock=23


### =====================================================
### 7. GOODS ISSUE — stock decreases
### =====================================================

### Issue P1/W1 qty=3
### expect: S1 CurrentStock 35 → 32, AvailableStock 33 → 30
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/goodsIssue
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P1",
  "warehouseID": "W1",
  "qty": 3,
  "movedBy": "CoachA"
}

###

### Issue P3/W1 qty=10
### expect: S5 CurrentStock 100 → 90
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/goodsIssue
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P3",
  "warehouseID": "W1",
  "qty": 10,
  "movedBy": "CoachB"
}

###

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/StockLevels
### verify: S1 CurrentStock=32, S5 CurrentStock=90


### =====================================================
### 8. STOCK TRANSFER — deduct source, add destination
### =====================================================

### Transfer P2 from W1 → W2, qty=10
### expect: S3 CurrentStock 50 → 40, S4 CurrentStock 0 → 10
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/stockTransfer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P2",
  "fromWarehouse": "W1",
  "toWarehouse": "W2",
  "qty": 10,
  "movedBy": "ManagerA"
}

###

### Transfer P5 from W2 → W1, qty=5
### expect: S9 CurrentStock 20 → 15, S8 CurrentStock 5 → 10
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/stockTransfer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P5",
  "fromWarehouse": "W2",
  "toWarehouse": "W1",
  "qty": 5,
  "movedBy": "ManagerA"
}

###

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/StockLevels
### verify: S3=40, S4=10, S8=10, S9=15


### =====================================================
### 9. EDGE CASES — must all fail cleanly
### =====================================================

### 400 — insufficient stock on goodsIssue
### expect: 400 "Insufficient stock. Available: 30, Requested: 999"
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/goodsIssue
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P1",
  "warehouseID": "W1",
  "qty": 999,
  "movedBy": "TestUser"
}

###

### 404 — invalid product on goodsReceipt
### expect: 404 "Stock not found"
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/goodsReceipt
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "INVALID",
  "warehouseID": "W1",
  "qty": 10,
  "movedBy": "TestUser"
}

###

### 400 — insufficient stock on stockTransfer
### expect: 400 "Insufficient stock"
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/stockTransfer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P2",
  "fromWarehouse": "W1",
  "toWarehouse": "W2",
  "qty": 9999,
  "movedBy": "TestUser"
}

###

### 404 — invalid destination warehouse on stockTransfer
### expect: 404 "Stock not found in destination warehouse INVALID"
POST http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/stockTransfer
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productID": "P2",
  "fromWarehouse": "W1",
  "toWarehouse": "INVALID",
  "qty": 5,
  "movedBy": "TestUser"
}

###

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/StockLevels
### verify: numbers unchanged after all 4 error cases above


### =====================================================
### 10. VERIFY FINAL STATE
### =====================================================

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/movement/StockMovements
### expect: only the SUCCESSFUL movements — 2 receipts + 2 issues + 2 transfers = 6 records
### the 4 error cases above must NOT appear here

###

GET http://localhost:4004/odata/v4/inventory/StockLevels
### final expected state:
### S1  P1/W1  CurrentStock=32  ReservedStock=2   AvailableStock=30
### S2  P1/W2  CurrentStock=10  ReservedStock=0   AvailableStock=10
### S3  P2/W1  CurrentStock=40  ReservedStock=5   AvailableStock=35
### S4  P2/W2  CurrentStock=10  ReservedStock=0   AvailableStock=10
### S5  P3/W1  CurrentStock=90  ReservedStock=10  AvailableStock=80
### S6  P3/W2  CurrentStock=40  ReservedStock=5   AvailableStock=35
### S7  P4/W1  CurrentStock=23  ReservedStock=0   AvailableStock=23
### S8  P5/W1  CurrentStock=10  ReservedStock=1   AvailableStock=9
### S9  P5/W2  CurrentStock=15  ReservedStock=0   AvailableStock=15